```yaml
        type: SystemAssigned
    kind: string
    location: string
    lockbox:
        state: string
    networkInjection:
        virtualNetworks:
            nextLink: string
            value:
                - id: string
                  subnet:
                    name: string
    resourceGroupName: string
    tags:
        string: string
```

</pulumi-choosable>
</div>

        <span class="property-type"><a href="#subnetpropertiesresponse">Property Map</a></span>
    </dt>
    <dd>Properties of a subnet.</dd></dl>
</pulumi-choosable>
</div>

## Import



An existing resource can be imported using its type token, name, and identifier, e.g.

```sh
$ pulumi import azure-native:powerplatform:EnterprisePolicy enterprisePolicy /subscriptions/{subscriptionId}/resourceGroups/{resourceGroupName}/providers/Microsoft.PowerPlatform/enterprisePolicies/{enterprisePolicyName} 
```


To learn more about importing existing cloud resources, see [Importing resources](/docs/using-pulumi/adopting-pulumi/import/).
